RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 7000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY RANGER away well, hustled to clear, established inside position, continued to hold rail on the turn, kicked away late on the turn and won convincingly. ABBEY OOPS tracked leaders along the rail on the backstretch, continued along the inside on the turn, entered lane in the three path and kept on to save second. CUTE RENEGADE away cleanly, unhurried early, dropped back on a loose reign, continued to trail on the turn, advanced in the three path, eased to the rail in the lane and made a mild rally along the rail. HAMPTONRUN broke a touch slow, hustled to try and take command, had to settle for a chasing two wide position, had to be asked to keep up on the turn and offered little in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Ranger
ENTRY.OWNER: Garcia Juan Manuel Salgado Carlos Abel Torres Gustavo Alejandro and Zubieta Lore

ENTRY.NAME: Cute Renegade
ENTRY.OWNER: Conner Dennis Jacobsen Wade and McKeen Michael
